+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01N91s9B1Ght97LdDbThNdCC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Versioned Document Store with Structural Merge\n     2→\n     3→Build an in-memory versioned document store -- think \"Git for JSON documents.\" The library should support CRUD operations on JSON documents, version history, branching, and three-way structural merging between branches.\n     4→\n     5→## API\n     6→\n     7→Export a `DocumentStore` class (or factory function) from `src/index.ts` with the following interface:\n     8→\n     9→```typescript\n    10→interface DocumentStore {\n    11→  // Document CRUD\n    12→  create(id: string, content: object): void;\n    13→  get(id: string): object;\n    14→  update(id: string, content: object): void;\n    15→  delete(id: string): void;\n    16→\n    17→  // Version history\n    18→  getHistory(id: string): Version[];\n    19→  getVersion(id: string, versionId: string): object;\n    20→\n    21→  // Branching\n    22→  createBranch(name: string, fromBranch?: string): void;\n    23→  switchBranch(name: string): void;\n    24→  getBranch(): string;\n    25→  listBranches(): string[];\n    26→\n    27→  // Merging\n    28→  merge(sourceBranch: string): MergeResult;\n    29→}\n    30→\n    31→interface Version {\n    32→  id: string;\n    33→  timestamp: number;\n    34→  content: object;\n    35→}\n    36→\n    37→interface MergeResult {\n    38→  merged: Record<string, object>;  // documentId -> merged content\n    39→  conflicts: Conflict[];\n    40→  applied: boolean;  // true if merge was auto-applied (no conflicts)\n    41→}\n    42→\n    43→interface Conflict {\n    44→  documentId: string;\n    45→  path: string;       // dot-separated JSON path, e.g. \"a.b.c\"\n    46→  base: any;\n    47→  ours: any;\n    48→  theirs: any;\n    49→}\n    50→```\n    51→\n    52→## Behavior\n    53→\n    54→### Documents\n    55→- `create(id, content)` stores a new document. Throws if the ID already exists on the current branch.\n    56→- `get(id)` returns the current content. Throws if the document doesn't exist or has been deleted.\n    57→- `update(id, content)` replaces the document content and creates a new version. Throws if the document doesn't exist.\n    58→- `delete(id)` removes a document from the current branch. Throws if it doesn't exist.\n    59→\n    60→### Version History\n    61→- Every `create` and `update` generates a new version with a unique `id`, a `timestamp`, and the full document `content` at that point.\n    62→- `getHistory(id)` returns versions in chronological order (oldest first).\n    63→- `getVersion(id, versionId)` returns the content at a specific version.\n    64→\n    65→### Branching\n    66→- The default branch is `\"main\"`.\n    67→- `createBranch(name)` creates a new branch from the current branch's current state. If `fromBranch` is provided, branch from that branch instead.\n    68→- `switchBranch(name)` switches the active branch. All subsequent CRUD operations apply to that branch.\n    69→- Changes on one branch are not visible on other branches.\n    70→\n    71→### Merging\n    72→- `merge(sourceBranch)` merges changes from `sourceBranch` into the current branch.\n    73→- Uses **three-way merge**: find the common ancestor state (the point where the branches diverged), then compare both branches against that base.\n    74→- For each document that changed on either branch:\n    75→  - If only one side changed a field, take that change (no conflict).\n    76→  - If both sides changed the same field to the **same** value, no conflict.\n    77→  - If both sides changed the same field to **different** values, that's a conflict.\n    78→- If there are **no conflicts**, the merge is auto-applied to the current branch (`applied: true`), and the `merged` field contains the resulting document contents.\n    79→- If there **are conflicts**, the merge is **not** applied (`applied: false`), and the conflicts are returned so the caller can resolve them. The current branch remains unchanged.\n    80→- The `merged` field always contains the merge result (with conflicts resolved in favor of \"ours\" for the purpose of showing what it would look like).\n    81→- A merge with no changes on either side is a no-op (fast-forward).\n    82→\n    83→## Constraints\n    84→- All operations are synchronous and in-memory.\n    85→- Documents are plain JSON objects (no arrays at the top level, though fields may contain arrays).\n    86→- Deep clone document contents on storage and retrieval to prevent mutation.\n    87→- The store must handle multiple documents independently -- changes to different documents on different branches should merge cleanly with no conflicts.\n    88→\n    89→## Project Structure\n    90→\n    91→Put your implementation in `src/`. The entry point is `src/index.ts`. You may split into multiple files if you wish.\n    92→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011aSojzmzTdxCMohV4uasny","session_id":"0d5674de-076a-4f1f-812c-af9859c500ee","uuid":"92cf6e51-ada8-46f9-9140-c36ae0adf1f2"}
